title: Add entries for existing packages to README
Add Arch linux notes
body:
I had `pcscd` already installed, but age-plugin-yubikey didn't work initially.

I installed `pcsc-tools` so I could do `pcsc_scan`, which also found nothing. Then I installed `yubikey-manager` so I could `ykman info`, which worked, but after that magically pcsc_scan and age-plugin-yubikey were working too.

Not sure if installing `yubikey-manager` had to do with it, but anyway.

title: Add installation instructions for Fedora Linux
body: Add entries in the README to get the PC/SC dependency ready under Fedora.

title: Update release workflow
body:
- `ubuntu-18.04` runner has been deprecated and removed by GitHub. We now use `ubuntu-20.04`.
- `actions-rs/toolchain` is replaced by `dtolnay/rust-toolchain`.

title: Clarify significance of the age identity file
body: Replaces str4d/age-plugin-yubikey#122.

title: Provide a better error message when management key authentication fails
body:
We now indicate to the user that AES management key algorithms are not yet supported, and tell them how to change their management key to use TDES.

Closes str4d/age-plugin-yubikey#135.

title: Intercept PIN errors and replace with PUK errors as necessary
body: Once iqlusioninc/yubikey.rs#479 is part of a `yubikey` release we can migrate to, this will mean that users get correctly notified of incorrect PUK entry, instead of being told it is an incorrect PIN issue.

title: Explicitly mention CCID packages for the two BSDs
body: As mentioned in #112, the ccid/libccid packages may need to be installed for a yubikey to be recognized on OpenBSD and FreeBSD. That escaped me in my first patch.

title: Ignore smart cards that don't have a PIV applet
body:
Depends on iqlusioninc/yubikey.rs#476.

Closes str4d/age-plugin-yubikey#78.

title: Document and warn that PIN policy "Once" doesn't work for YubiKey 4
body: Part of #115.

title: Prevent changing the default PIN to itself
body: Closes str4d/age-plugin-yubikey#120.

title: Enforce correct PIN lengths during YubiKey setup
body: The behaviour of `age-plugin-yubikey` during setup now matches its behaviour during plugin usage.

title: Treat `pcsc::Error::NoSmartcard` as a "YubiKey disconnected" error
body:
Some SmartCard readers report this error when no SmartCard is inserted, so we need to check for it when filtering for connected YubiKeys (along with `pcsc::Error::RemovedCard` which some _other_ SmartCard readers report instead).

Closes str4d/age-plugin-yubikey#81.

title: Request PIN before certificate generation if PIN policy is "always"
body:
We also correctly ask for a PIN touch after the key is generated (which does not need it) but before certificate generation (which does if the touch policy is not "none").

Closes str4d/age-plugin-yubikey#101.

title: docs: add brew install instructions
body: Just discovered this after manually installing from the releases page, so thought it would be useful to add to README.md

title: Add pcscd recommentation for {Open,Free}BSD
body: Include recommendations for OpenBSD and FreeBSD to remedy the error when pcscd is not running.

title: Extend "sharing violation" logic to send SIGHUP to `yubikey-agent` processes
body: Closes #94.

title: Clarify that non-TDES management keys are unsupported
body: Supporting them is blocked on iqlusioninc/yubikey.rs#330.

title: Give guidance on reconfiguring YubiKeys with unprotected management keys
body: Closes str4d/age-plugin-yubikey#21.

title: Stop scdaemon if it is holding exclusive access to a YubiKey
body: Closes str4d/age-plugin-yubikey#82.

title: CI: Build release binaries for Apple ARM64
body: Closes str4d/age-plugin-yubikey#71.

title: Inform users when `pcscd` is required
body: Closes str4d/age-plugin-yubikey#83.

body: Closes str4d/age-plugin-yubikey#42.

title: Don't print message if YubiKey is waiting for touch
body: The user call-to-action will instead be implemented on the client side, where it can be done in a more forgiving way (allowing the user some time to react before prompting them that it is waiting on the plugin).

title: Enable users to skip YubiKeys at plugging-in time
body: This requires the `confirm` plugin command to be supported by the age client; otherwise we fall back to the previous message-plus-timer method.
